About the job
Banco de Investimento Global (BiG) is an independent Iberian investment bank. BiG’s Corporate Finance team delivers financial advisory services in Mergers & Acquisitions (M&A) and Capital Markets transactions.

BiG is recruiting an Analyst to join its Madrid Corporate Finance team and support the growing business in Spain and international markets.

The Selected Candidate Will Assume The Following Main Responsibilities

Participation in new business initiatives, including preparing pitchbooks and proposals to companies and international investors;
Preparing and participating in commercial activity, such as prospecting, commercial contacts and meetings with clients and potential clients;
Execution of M&A deals, involving industry analysis, financial modelling, company valuation and deal structuring;
Creating, reviewing and perfecting different company presentations materials, such as Teasers, Information Memoranda, Management Presentations, etc..

What's On Offer

The selected candidate will have the opportunity to be part of dynamic Iberian team, to work on midmarket transactions and to support BiG’s ambitious strategy for the Spanish market. This is an excellent opportunity for any individual looking to embrace new challenges and further their career within a growing financial institution.

Work base: Madrid

Requisitos mínimos

Expected Skills And Experience Include

Degree in BA or Economy. Masters in Finance or MBA will be valued;
Previous experience in investment banking, M&A or consulting will be valued;
Strong analytical, communication and teamwork skills;
Strong academic background / results and financial knowledge (accounting and company valuation) and understanding of financial statements;
Entrepreneurial spirit with the ability to contribute your own ideas and work autonomously;
Proficiency in the use of Excel, Power Point, Word and Outlook;
Fluency in Spanish and English;
Attention to detail.

If you have the motivation to make a difference and want to be part of a dynamic organisation with a strong culture of compliance, please respond to this advert.
